.TH LVIBE 1 "2026" "Linux" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lvibe \- Lé Vibe launcher (managed Ollama + Code OSS editor)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lvibe
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ editor_args " ...]"
.SH DESCRIPTION
Same program as
.BR le\-vibe (1).
Launches the Lé Vibe session: optional product first\-run bootstrap,
starts a dedicated\-port \fBollama serve\fR, then your editor (defaults in
\fBle_vibe.launcher\fR: \fBLE_VIBE_EDITOR\fR if set, else \fB/usr/lib/le-vibe/bin/codium\fR,
else \fB/usr/bin/codium\fR, else \fBcodium\fR on \fBPATH\fR). On exit, stops the
managed Ollama process so GPU VRAM is released.
.PP
Open the current project in the editor:
.B lvibe \.
.PP
Product naming: Lé Vibe is not Microsoft Visual Studio Code; use Code \-
OSS / VSCodium\-class editors.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B lvibe sync-agent-skills
.RI [ workspace ]
Copy missing agent skill templates into \fB.lvibe/agents/<agent_id>/skill.md\fR (e.g. after upgrading the \fBle\-vibe\fR stack). \fIworkspace\fR defaults to the current directory; \fB.lvibe/\fR must already exist. Does not start Ollama or the editor.
.TP
.B lvibe open-welcome
.RI [ workspace ]
Open \fB.lvibe/WELCOME.md\fR (PRODUCT_SPEC §4) in the editor. \fIworkspace\fR defaults to the current directory; \fB.lvibe/\fR must already exist from a prior consent\-gated open. Does not start Ollama or first\-run bootstrap.
.TP
.B lvibe apply\-opening\-skip
.RI [ workspace ]
Advance \fBsession\-manifest.json\fR when \fBmeta.current_step_id\fR is \fBopening_intent\fR (skip hook). \fBdocs/SESSION_ORCHESTRATION_SPEC.md\fR STEP 2.
.TP
.B lvibe hygiene
.RI [ hygiene_options ]
Validate \fB.lvibe/\fR manifest, session JSON, and chunk path refs — same as \fBpython3 \-m le_vibe.hygiene\fR and \fBlvibe\-hygiene\fR(1). See \fBle\-vibe\fR(1) for the stack install.
.TP
.B lvibe logs
.RI [ \-\-path\-only | \-\-tail " N " ]
Show the local structured log path (\fB~/.config/le\-vibe/le\-vibe.log.jsonl\fR) and optional \fBtail\fR\-style last \fIN\fR lines. Local JSON Lines only — \fBdocs/privacy\-and\-telemetry.md\fR.
.TP
.B lvibe continue-pin
.RI [ \-\-path\-only ]
Print the pinned Open VSX semver for Continue (\fBcontinue.continue@\fIver\fR). Pin file: \fB/usr/share/le\-vibe/continue\-openvsx\-version\fR when installed, else monorepo \fBpackaging/continue\-openvsx\-version\fR; \fBLE_VIBE_CONTINUE_PIN_FILE\fR overrides. \fBdocs/continue\-extension\-pin.md\fR.
.TP
.B lvibe verify-checksums
.RI [ \-C " dir " ]
Run \fBsha256sum \-c SHA256SUMS\fR in a release directory (artifact extract). \fBdocs/apt\-repo\-releases.md\fR (H1).
.TP
.B lvibe pip-audit
.RI [ pip\-audit_options ]
Run \fBpip\-audit \-r\fR against \fBle\-vibe/requirements.txt\fR in a git clone (\fBpip install pip\-audit\fR). Not available when the stack \fB.deb\fR omits \fBrequirements.txt\fR — \fBdocs/sbom\-signing\-audit.md\fR (H2).
.TP
.B lvibe ci-smoke
.RI [ args ]
Run \fBpackaging/scripts/ci\-smoke.sh\fR from the monorepo root (\fBLE_VIBE_REPO_ROOT\fR or parent walk). \fBdocs/ci\-qa\-hardening.md\fR (H3).
.TP
.B lvibe ci\-editor\-gate
.RI [ args ]
Run \fBpackaging/scripts/ci\-editor\-gate.sh\fR (same as \fB./editor/smoke.sh\fR gate). \fBdocs/ci\-qa\-hardening.md\fR (H3).
.TP
.B lvibe brand-paths
.RI [ \-\-path\-only ]
Print paths to canonical \fBle\-vibe.svg\fR (monorepo \fBpackaging/icons/...\fR and/or \fB/usr/share/icons/...\fR when installed). \fBdocs/brand\-assets.md\fR (H5).
.TP
.B lvibe product\-surface
.RI [ \-\-path\-only " KEY " ]
List \fB.github/\fR CI, Dependabot, issue \fBconfig.yml\fR, \fBdocs/README.md\fR, privacy, \fBSECURITY.md\fR. \fBdocs/PM_STAGE_MAP.md\fR STEP 12 (H8).
.TP
.B lvibe flatpak\-appimage
.RI [ \-\-path\-only " KEY " ]
List \fBdocs/flatpak\-appimage.md\fR, \fBpackaging/flatpak/\fR manifest, \fBpackaging/appimage/\fR scripts. \fBdocs/PM_STAGE_MAP.md\fR STEP 13 (H7).
.TP
.B lvibe ide\-prereqs
.RI [ \-\-path\-only " KEY " ]
§7.3 IDE \fB.deb\fR packaging paths and whether \fBeditor/vscodium/VSCode\-linux\-*\fR exists. \fBdocs/PM_STAGE_MAP.md\fR STEP 14 (H6).
.SH OPTIONS
See
.BR le\-vibe (1).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/le\-vibe/
Configs, first\-run marker, welcome marker (\fB.welcome\-shown\fR), managed Ollama state,
\fBmodel\-decision.json\fR, \fBlock\-model.json\fR (concrete Ollama tag lock), \fBcontinue\-config.yaml\fR.
.TP
.I .lvibe/
Per\-project workspace memory \fBafter\fR consent on first open (e.g. \fBlvibe .\fR); see \fBle\-vibe\fR(1) and \fI/usr/share/doc/le\-vibe/README.Debian\fR.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR le\-vibe (1),
.BR le\-vibe\-setup\-continue (1),
.BR codium (1),
.BR ollama (1).
Full docs: \fI/usr/share/doc/le-vibe/README.Debian\fR.
